This module is a derivative work of java-ascii-render
(https://github.com/indvd00m/java-ascii-render), copyright (c) indvd00m
<gotoindvdum at gmail dot com>, also licensed under the Apache License,
Version 2.0.

The original library targets Java 1.6 and uses package
com.indvd00m.ascii.render.* . This derivative work has been:

  - Repackaged under io.jaiclaw.asciirender.*
  - Modernized for Java 21 (records for value types; for-each and
    stream idioms in place of indexed loops; cleaner generic types)
  - Trimmed: the AWT-backed PseudoText element and the
    Render.setPseudoCanvas(boolean) flag are not included
  - Extended: an McpToolProvider implementation lets the renderer be
    reached over JaiClaw's MCP server endpoint when jaiclaw-gateway is
    on the classpath

The underlying rendering algorithms (Bresenham line/circle, axis
normalization, word-wrap-with-truncation in Text, table cell layout)
are unchanged in spirit from the upstream library; original author
credit goes to indvd00m.
